news.title: China's Shenzhen state shareholders show liquidity support for Vanke
news.para: Vanke's bonds and shares have seen big selloffs since late October due to weak investor confidence and liquidity worries after defaults from string of developers including China Evergrande Group and Country Garden following the sector's slide into a debt crisis in mid-2021.

news.title: State support for China Vanke does little for property sector, analysts say
news.para: Hang Seng Mainland Properties Index dropped 2.6% on Tuesday, with Vanke's Hong Kong-listed shares easing more than 1%. That compared to gains of 3.4% and 7.2% respectively on Monday on news of a potential deal to shore up Vanke's finances.

news.title: Wave of cancellations in German housing construction at new high: Ifo
news.para: In October, 22.2% percent of companies reported cancelled projects, up from 21.4% the previous month, the Ifo economic institute said.

news.title: Arihant Superstructure's net profit increases by 35.90% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Arihant Superstructure's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 109.04 crore in Q2 FY24, a dip of 9.79 per cent from Rs 120.88 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Eldeco Housing and Industries' net profit declines 27.82% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Eldeco Housing and Industries' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 18.65 crore in Q2 FY24, a dip of 48.02 per cent from Rs 35.88 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shree Cement's net profit increases by 143.73% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Shree Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 4,932.11 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 17.50 per cent from Rs 4,197.37 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Mumbai AQI: Most realty construction going on in western suburbs
news.para: ​From January 1, 2021 to November 1, 2023, developers in R-central received 515 further commencement certificates (FCCs) and 277 commencement certificates (CCs). The corresponding numbers for K-East were 436 and 198 (see graphic for details and definitions).

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA set to hire consultant for door-to-door land survey
news.para: “The survey is aimed at checking if the official record of land acquisition, purchases, allotments, and resumptions matches the on-ground observations. Additionally, it will also help in checking instances of land encroachments,” said a GNIDA official.

news.title: Kamdhenu Ventures posts net profit of Rs 3.42 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Kamdhenu Ventures' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 65.94 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 2.26 per cent from Rs 64.48 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body starts property digitization in four wards
news.para: According to senior officials from BBMP’s revenue department, they have already started digitization of property documents in four wards — Kodigehalli, CV Raman Nagar, Horamavu, and Arakere — and will complete it for all the wards within three months.

news.title: Man lnfraconstruction's net profit increases by 30.72% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Man lnfraconstruction's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 242.85 crore in Q2 FY24, a dip of 41.33 per cent from Rs 413.91 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Maharashtra: MPCB officials start dust checks at construction sites to curb pollution
news.para: The Maharashtra Pollution Control Board (MPCB) issued directions in this regard last week. The officials have started the checks in Mumbai and are expected to follow suit in Pune in the days to come.

news.title: Mumbai Air Pollution: MPCB issues notices to four concrete mixing plants for polluting air
news.para: These notices, called 'compliance notices,' have been issued under the Air Pollution and Control of Prevention Act, 1981 to S P Singla Construction, J Kumar Infra Projects Ltd, Resonant Realtors Projects Pvt Ltd and Lonavala Construction Company.

news.title: RR Kabel's net profit grows by 111.69% in Q2 FY24
news.para: RR Kabel's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,624.43 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 17.99 per cent from Rs 1,376.72 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: DB Realty divests 100% stake in Real Gem Buildtech for about Rs 231.42 crore
news.para: Consequent upon the aforesaid sale, Real Gem Buildtech will cease to be a wholly owned subsidiary of DB Realty. The transaction will lead to considerable amount of free cashflow to the company.

news.title: UltraTech Cement receives order for GST demand & penalty worth Rs 2.28 crore
news.para: UltraTech Cement will seek legal recourse to contest the above order since the differential duty with interest was already deposited, but has not been taken cognizance of by the authority.

news.title: Law proposed to regulate housing societies in Gujarat
news.para: An authority may be established to oversee housing societies, as the current registrar of cooperatives lacks the manpower to handle their matters. Additionally, many residential housing societies have not had their accounts audited for years.

news.title: Bengaluru development body told to register project with Karnataka-RERA
news.para: The directive came in K-RERA’s interim order on November 3, while hearing a complaint filed by a site allottee seeking relief of interest on the delay period and direction to the promoter to complete the project.

news.title: Gurugram: Building plans filed, town planner told to speed up structural audit of highrises
news.para: The ADC directed DTP to immediately share estimates with the concerned builder management so that the audit work can be started and completed as soon as possible.

news.title: No registration for 182 realty projects, says MahaRERA
news.para: Promoters of as many as 222 projects had requested the MahaRera to lift the suspension by stating that they had not only paid the penalty, but also updated their quarterly progress reports.
